Provenance statement (Invariant I7)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

entrypoint is an independent, clean-room implementation. As of Phase 0 it
contains NO source code copied or derived from Entire (github.com/entireio/cli)
or any other agent-checkpointing product. The comparison to Entire in README.md
is editorial positioning only, not a code lineage.

The concepts entrypoint implements natively — git-notes-attached work packets,
the `Entrypoint-Packet` commit trailer, Meshwire range validation — were
written for this repository and carry only the copyright above.

If, in a later phase, any file becomes derived from a third party's licensed
code, that file must (a) preserve the upstream copyright + license header and
(b) be recorded in THIRD_PARTY.md before it is merged.

Third-party dependencies redistributed in built binaries are listed, with their
licenses, in THIRD_PARTY.md.
